msgid ""
"Content of ``...`` when the property is exported using :command:"
"`install(EXPORT)`, and empty otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3245
msgid ""
"Content of ``...`` when the property is exported using :command:`export`, or "
"when the target is used by another target in the same buildsystem. Expands "
"to the empty string otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3253
msgid ""
"Content of ``...`` when the target is used by another target in the same "
"buildsystem. Expands to the empty string otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3258
msgid ""
"Content of the install prefix when the target is exported via :command:"
"`install(EXPORT)`, or when evaluated in the :prop_tgt:`INSTALL_NAME_DIR` "
"property or the ``INSTALL_NAME_DIR`` argument of :command:"
"`install(RUNTIME_DEPENDENCY_SET)`, and empty otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3263
msgid ""
"Evaluates to the content of the install prefix in the code argument of :"
"command:`install(CODE)` or the file argument of :command:`install(SCRIPT)`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3269
msgid "Multi-level Expression Evaluation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3275
msgid ""
"Content of ``expr`` evaluated as a generator expression in the current "
"context. This enables consumption of generator expressions whose evaluation "
"results itself in generator expressions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3283
msgid ""
"Content of ``expr`` evaluated as a generator expression in the context of "
"``tgt`` target. This enables consumption of custom target properties that "
"themselves contain generator expressions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3287
msgid ""
"Having the capability to evaluate generator expressions is very useful when "
"you want to manage custom properties supporting generator expressions. For "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3291
msgid ""
"add_library(foo ...)\n"
"\n"
"set_property(TARGET foo PROPERTY\n"
"  CUSTOM_KEYS $<$<CONFIG:DEBUG>:FOO_EXTRA_THINGS>\n"
")\n"
"\n"
"add_custom_target(printFooKeys\n"
"  COMMAND ${CMAKE_COMMAND} -E echo $<TARGET_PROPERTY:foo,CUSTOM_KEYS>\n"
")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3303
msgid ""
"This naive implementation of the ``printFooKeys`` custom command is wrong "
"because ``CUSTOM_KEYS`` target property is not evaluated and the content is "
"passed as is (i.e. ``$<$<CONFIG:DEBUG>:FOO_EXTRA_THINGS>``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3307
msgid ""
"To have the expected result (i.e. ``FOO_EXTRA_THINGS`` if config is "
"``Debug``), it is required to evaluate the output of ``$<TARGET_PROPERTY:foo,"
"CUSTOM_KEYS>``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3311
msgid ""
"add_custom_target(printFooKeys\n"
"  COMMAND ${CMAKE_COMMAND} -E\n"
"    echo $<TARGET_GENEX_EVAL:foo,$<TARGET_PROPERTY:foo,CUSTOM_KEYS>>\n"
")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3319
msgid "Escaped Characters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3321
msgid ""
"These expressions evaluate to specific string literals. Use them in place of "
"the actual string literal where you need to prevent them from having their "
"special meaning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3327
msgid ""
"A literal ``>``. Used for example to compare strings that contain a ``>``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3331
msgid ""
"A literal ``,``. Used for example to compare strings which contain a ``,``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3335
msgid ""
"A literal ``;``. Used to prevent list expansion on an argument with ``;``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3341
msgid ""
"A literal ``\"``. Used to allow string literal quotes inside a generator "
"expression."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3345
msgid "Deprecated Expressions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-generator-expressions.7.rst:3349
msgid ""
"Configuration name. Deprecated since CMake 3.0. Use :genex:`CONFIG` instead."
msgstr ""
